What did he want?

266
00:26:05,009 --> 00:26:06,610
He wants her to call him.

267
00:26:17,534 --> 00:26:21,997
You've reached Universal Exports.
Our offices are currently closed.

268
00:26:23,867 --> 00:26:25,600
Pay attention next time.

269
00:26:29,755 --> 00:26:32,132
And you can do all this for me?

270
00:26:33,133 --> 00:26:36,095
Well, look at what we did to this country.

271
00:26:36,178 --> 00:26:37,638
The Haitians elect a priest

272
00:26:37,721 --> 00:26:41,451
who decides to raise the minimum
wage from 38 cents to $1 a day.

273
00:26:41,517 --> 00:26:42,518
Whoa.

274
00:26:42,601 --> 00:26:46,021
It's not a lot, but it's enough
to upset the corporations

275
00:26:46,105 --> 00:26:49,566
who were here making
T-shirts and running shoes.

276
00:26:49,650 --> 00:26:53,737
So they called us, and
we facilitated a change.

277
00:26:53,821 --> 00:26:54,905
The difference is,

278
00:26:54,988 --> 00:26:59,118
my country's not some flyspeck
in the middle of the Caribbean.

279
00:26:59,201 --> 00:27:02,621
But we've already begun
destabilising the government.

280
00:27:02,704 --> 00:27:05,124
We'll supply the private security.

281
00:27:05,207 --> 00:27:07,417
We'll pay off the right officials,

282
00:27:07,501 --> 00:27:11,463
and we have 26 countries ready
to officially recognise

283
00:27:11,547 --> 00:27:14,049
your new Bolivian government.

284
00:27:15,050 --> 00:27:17,261
You want your country back.

285
00:27:17,636 --> 00:27:20,973
My organisation can give
it to you within the week.

286
00:27:23,016 --> 00:27:24,685
You've been busy.

287
00:27:25,060 --> 00:27:27,521
And in return you want what?

288
00:27:28,689 --> 00:27:30,107
A desert.

289
00:27:37,197 --> 00:27:39,783
- This part.
- This land is worthless.

290
00:27:41,743 --> 00:27:43,787
So you're getting a great deal.

291
00:27:43,871 --> 00:27:45,831
You won't find oil there.

292
00:27:45,914 --> 00:27:47,958
Everyone has tried.

293
00:27:48,041 --> 00:27:50,419
Maybe, maybe not.

294
00:27:51,336 --> 00:27:54,256
But we own whatever we find.

295
00:28:01,722 --> 00:28:04,600
Did you know Ernesto Monies'?

296
00:28:04,683 --> 00:28:07,102
A very powerful man in his day.

297
00:28:07,186 --> 00:28:09,646
He had a beautiful Russian wife.

298
00:28:10,564 --> 00:28:11,899
A dancer.

299
00:28:12,774 --> 00:28:15,194
Well, his daughter works for me.

300
00:28:15,777 --> 00:28:17,070
Or did.

301
00:28:17,738 --> 00:28:19,239
She's lovely,

302
00:28:19,781 --> 00:28:21,867
but I don't see the resemblance.

303
00:28:21,950 --> 00:28:25,787
Why don't you consider her as
something to sweeten the deal?

304
00:28:28,707 --> 00:28:32,628
Just promise me to drop her
over the side when you're done.

305
00:28:34,254 --> 00:28:36,924
Camille, General Medrano.

306
00:28:45,414 --> 00:28:47,007
I knew your family.

307
00:28:48,033 --> 00:28:51,103
Sadly, I believe I was the
last to see them alive.

308
00:28:52,814 --> 00:28:55,567
Be careful what you wish for, my dear.

309
00:29:04,785 --> 00:29:06,078
Have fun, you two.

310
00:30:25,240 --> 00:30:26,283
What the hell are you doing?

311
00:30:26,366 --> 00:30:28,410
- You're welcome.
- You idiot. Take me back.

312
00:30:28,493 --> 00:30:31,079
You know, maybe I'll do that later.

313
00:30:34,583 --> 00:30:36,752
You're not one of Greene's.

314
00:30:37,919 --> 00:30:39,504
Dominic Greene?

315
00:30:43,050 --> 00:30:44,384
Get down.

316
00:31:09,242 --> 00:31:11,495
- Give me the wheel.
- Navigate.

317
00:31:17,584 --> 00:31:18,710
Left.

318
00:31:29,721 --> 00:31:31,932
- What are you doing?
- Hold on.

319
00:31:48,782 --> 00:31:50,117
Get down.

320
00:33:09,905 --> 00:33:11,406
Excuse me.

321
00:33:11,490 --> 00:33:13,658
Thank you. She's seasick.

322
00:33:46,233 --> 00:33:47,692
It's Bond.

323
00:33:47,776 --> 00:33:49,861
- Connect Bond.
- Connecting 007.

324
00:33:49,945 --> 00:33:50,946
Yes?

325
00:33:51,029 --> 00:33:53,198
Name check, Dominic Greene.

326
00:33:53,281 --> 00:33:55,116
G-R-E-E-N-E.

327
00:33:57,744 --> 00:33:58,978
I might need a little more than that.

328
00:33:59,061 --> 00:34:00,228
There are a lot of Dominic Greenes.

329
00:34:00,229 --> 00:34:01,999
Do you have a social
security or passport number?

330
00:34:02,082 --> 00:34:03,375
No.

331
00:34:03,458 --> 00:34:04,793
Scanning DGSE databases.

332
00:34:04,876 --> 00:34:07,837
- Anything?
- Scanning KGB databases.

333
00:34:07,921 --> 00:34:10,090
Do you have anything? Will
you put her on, please?

334
00:34:10,173 --> 00:34:12,801
I am on, Bond. What
happened to Slate?

335
00:34:12,884 --> 00:34:14,052
I'm not dwelling on the past.

336
00:34:14,135 --> 00:34:15,581
I don't think you should, either.

337
00:34:15,582 --> 00:34:16,604
You killed him.

338
00:34:16,605 --> 00:34:19,391
Largest hit, Dominic Greene,
CEO of Greene Planet.

339
00:34:19,474 --> 00:34:21,351
It's a utility company,

340
00:34:21,434 --> 00:34:23,896
but Greene's been doing a
lot of philanthropic work,

341
00:34:23,979 --> 00:34:26,731
buying up large tracts of land
for ecological preserves.

342
00:34:26,815 --> 00:34:29,818
You should be getting his picture now.

343
00:34:29,901 --> 00:34:31,528
Yep, that's him.

344
00:34:32,070 --> 00:34:33,268
I'm afraid there's a firewall around

345
00:34:33,269 --> 00:34:34,331
his other corporate holdings,

346
00:34:34,332 --> 00:34:35,574
so we have no other information.

347
00:34:35,657 --> 00:34:37,075
Get me the Americans.

348
00:34:37,158 --> 00:34:38,577
Connecting.

349
00:34:38,660 --> 00:34:39,703
Go ahead.

350
00:34:39,786 --> 00:34:42,497
Interest in Dominic Greene, Greene Planet.

351
00:34:42,581 --> 00:34:44,332
Transferring you now.

352
00:34:46,251 --> 00:34:48,503
Hold for Gregory Beam, please.

353
00:34:49,421 --> 00:34:50,422
Thank you.

354
00:34:50,505 --> 00:34:52,424
Hi, this is Gregory Beam, ma'am.

355
00:34:52,507 --> 00:34:54,175
Hello, Mr Beam.

356
00:34:54,259 --> 00:34:57,846
I'm so sorry to keep you waiting.
We have no interest in Mr Greene.

357
00:34:57,929 --> 00:34:59,347
Thank you, Mr Beam.

358
00:34:59,431 --> 00:35:00,474
Connection terminated.

359
00:35:00,557 --> 00:35:02,350
He's a person of extreme interest.

360
00:35:02,434 --> 00:35:03,709
But he just said that he wasn't...

361
00:35:03,710 --> 00:35:04,811
Tanner, I asked about the man

362
00:35:04,894 --> 00:35:07,564
and she transferred me to the
section chief of South America.

363
00:35:07,647 --> 00:35:10,547
How would she know to do that
if they weren't tracking him?

364
00:35:15,196 --> 00:35:17,616
Bond, we have your location
as approaching an airfield.

365
00:35:17,699 --> 00:35:19,576
- Is Greene on the move?
- Yeah.

366
00:35:19,659 --> 00:35:22,829
I've got a tail number,
Golf-Zero-Charlie-Sierra-Charlie.

367
00:35:22,912 --> 00:35:23,962
Get me a destination.

368
00:35:27,709 --> 00:35:29,210
It's a private charter

369
00:35:29,294 --> 00:35:32,380
going to Bregenz, Austria,
leaving immediately.

370
00:35:32,922 --> 00:35:35,550
Tanner, authorise a charter for 007.

371
00:35:37,010 --> 00:35:40,138
And, Bond, if you could avoid
killing every possible lead,

372
00:35:40,221 --> 00:35:41,771
it would be deeply appreciated.

373
00:35:42,015 --> 00:35:44,225
Yes, ma'am. I'll do my best.

374
00:35:44,768 --> 00:35:46,394
Connection terminated.

375
00:35:46,478 --> 00:35:47,729
I've heard that before.

376
00:35:50,774 --> 00:35:52,108
- Hello.
- Hi.

377
00:35:52,567 --> 00:35:54,194
Welcome aboard.

378
00:35:57,405 --> 00:35:59,199
Come. Have a seat.

379
00:35:59,908 --> 00:36:02,035
Charlie-Sierra-Charlie.

380
00:36:17,258 --> 00:36:18,426
Jeez.

381
00:36:18,927 --> 00:36:20,261
Sorry.

382
00:36:23,932 --> 00:36:25,809
How much longer?

383
00:36:27,977 --> 00:36:30,063
So do we have an understanding?

384
00:36:31,147 --> 00:36:32,190
Yeah.

385
00:36:32,273 --> 00:36:34,651
We do nothing to stop a coup
in Bolivia, and in exchange,

386
00:36:34,734 --> 00:36:39,239
the new government gives America
the lease to any oil found.

387
00:36:40,657 --> 00:36:42,659
If it's oil you want.

388
00:36:43,702 --> 00:36:46,579
Well, you didn't find diamonds, did you?

389
00:36:52,085 --> 00:36:53,692
Drilling underground, you kept off

390
00:36:53,693 --> 00:36:55,631
everybody's radar for a very long time,

391
00:36:55,714 --> 00:36:59,884
but you can't buy that much piping
without somebody getting curious.

392
00:37:00,969 --> 00:37:02,971
We'll have to verify the find.

393
00:37:03,054 --> 00:37:05,069
I'm not even admitting there is

394
00:37:05,070 --> 00:37:07,475
one. You are getting
this for free.

395
00:37:08,476 --> 00:37:11,312
Venezuela, Brazil, now Bolivia.

396
00:37:11,396 --> 00:37:13,641
With you tied up in the Middle East,

397
00:37:13,642 --> 00:37:16,067
South America is falling like dominoes.

398
00:37:17,485 --> 00:37:19,783
You don't need another Marxist giving

399
00:37:19,784 --> 00:37:22,323
national resources to the people, do you?

400
00:37:22,991 --> 00:37:25,035
Well, we can hardly be expected
to do something about a coup

401
00:37:25,118 --> 00:37:27,036
we know nothing about.

402
00:37:30,498 --> 00:37:32,667
And I have a pest.

403
00:37:34,335 --> 00:37:35,503
This.

404
00:37:38,715 --> 00:37:41,176
You have any idea who that is?

405
00:37:51,269 --> 00:37:52,604
Sorry.

406
00:37:55,023 --> 00:37:57,776
It's James Bond, British Secret Service.

407
00:37:58,735 --> 00:38:01,654
I don't know how I could have missed that.

408
00:38:03,198 --> 00:38:05,950
I will need you to get rid of him for me.

409
00:38:06,034 --> 00:38:08,703
Yeah. That's not
gonna be a problem.

410
00:38:25,512 --> 00:38:27,639
You know who Greene is and you
wanna put us in bed with him.

411
00:38:27,722 --> 00:38:29,724
You are kidding, right?

412
00:38:29,808 --> 00:38:33,144
Yeah. You're right. We should
just deal with nice people.

413
00:38:33,228 --> 00:38:35,980
I need to know you're on the team, Felix.

414
00:38:36,064 --> 00:38:38,650
I need to know you value your career.

415
00:39:51,264 --> 00:39:52,891
Dominic Greene.

416
00:40:11,618 --> 00:40:13,411
- Good to see you. Good.
- How are you?

417
00:40:13,494 --> 00:40:14,913
Thank you.

418
00:40:49,822 --> 00:40:51,824
Ladies and gentlemen,

419
00:40:51,908 --> 00:40:55,370
tonight's performance of
Tosca will begin shortly.

420
00:40:55,453 --> 00:40:57,497
Please take your seats.

421
00:41:52,093 --> 00:41:54,804
What else does General Medrano require?

422
00:42:16,951 --> 00:42:19,412
Anything further from
Canadian intelligence?

423
00:42:19,495 --> 00:42:21,622
We'll discuss that later.

424
00:42:22,123 --> 00:42:24,459
How much more pipeline do we need?

425
00:42:24,542 --> 00:42:27,128
Ideally, 2,000 kilometres.

426
00:42:27,587 --> 00:42:29,630
Are there any objections?

427
00:42:30,798 --> 00:42:31,799
No.

428
00:42:31,883 --> 00:42:33,217
Not here.

429
00:42:33,301 --> 00:42:34,719
No objections.

430
00:42:35,344 --> 00:42:38,514
Transfer the funds from
our Siberian holdings.

431
00:42:38,598 --> 00:42:39,932
Done.

432
00:42:43,478 --> 00:42:45,438
Where do the Americans stand?

433
00:42:45,521 --> 00:42:47,738
Well, the CIA doesn't care about another

434
00:42:47,739 --> 00:42:49,901
dictator as long as they get their end.

435
00:42:49,984 --> 00:42:52,570
But when they find out
that they've been duped?

436
00:42:52,653 --> 00:42:54,572
I'm working on that.

437
00:42:54,655 --> 00:42:56,656
I'm still not sure that the Tierra Project

438
00:42:56,657 --> 00:42:58,284
is the best use of Quantum's time.

439
00:42:58,367 --> 00:43:00,745
Perhaps we should shift our
focus to the Canadian.

440
00:43:00,828 --> 00:43:03,581
This is the world's
most precious resource.

441
00:43:03,664 --> 00:43:06,918
We need to control as
much of it as we can.

442
00:43:07,001 --> 00:43:09,253
Bolivia must be top priority.

443
00:43:09,337 --> 00:43:11,255
Can I offer an opinion?

444
00:43:13,549 --> 00:43:17,512
I really think you people should
find a better place to meet.

445
00:43:23,142 --> 00:43:25,686
Where do you think you're going?

446
00:43:46,374 --> 00:43:47,959
Thank you.

447
00:43:57,885 --> 00:44:00,263
Well, Tosca isn't for everyone.

448
00:45:14,295 --> 00:45:15,671
Drop it.

449
00:45:19,258 --> 00:45:21,510
So who are you working for?

450
00:45:21,594 --> 00:45:22,845
Piss off.

451
00:45:23,221 --> 00:45:27,266
Get rid of anything we brought
with us. We've been compromised.

452
00:45:30,269 --> 00:45:32,980
I asked you who you were working for.

453
00:45:44,867 --> 00:45:47,286
- Is he one of ours?
- No.

454
00:45:47,370 --> 00:45:49,997
Then he shouldn't be looking at me.

455
00:45:58,631 --> 00:46:00,132
Get me M.

456
00:46:01,592 --> 00:46:02,927
It's your line.

457
00:46:03,010 --> 00:46:05,429
Thanks. Connect call.

458
00:46:05,513 --> 00:46:06,931
Connecting Tanner.

459
00:46:07,014 --> 00:46:08,474
We've ID 'd the pictures.

460
00:46:08,557 --> 00:46:09,850
Show me.

461
00:46:09,934 --> 00:46:12,334
Gregor Karakov, former minister, now

462
00:46:12,335 --> 00:46:14,605
owns most of the mines in Siberia,

463
00:46:14,689 --> 00:46:18,359
Moishe Soref, former
Mossad, now telecom giant,

464
00:46:18,442 --> 00:46:21,237
and Guy Haines, special envoy
to the Prime Minister.

465
00:46:21,320 --> 00:46:22,613
Get Bond.

466
00:46:22,697 --> 00:46:24,448
There's something else.

467
00:46:24,532 --> 00:46:26,274
It appears Bond shot Haines'

468
00:46:26,275 --> 00:46:28,577
bodyguard and threw him off a roof.

469
00:46:32,665 --> 00:46:34,417
- Where are you?
- Did you get my pictures?

470
00:46:34,500 --> 00:46:36,794
Was this a conversation?
Can you link these people?

471
00:46:36,877 --> 00:46:38,254
Is that stress in your voice?

472
00:46:38,337 --> 00:46:39,881
I need you to come in and debrief.

473
00:46:39,964 --> 00:46:41,057
I don't have time.

474
00:46:41,058 --> 00:46:43,134
Bond, you killed a man in Bregenz.

475
00:46:43,217 --> 00:46:44,427
I did my best not to.

476
00:46:44,510 --> 00:46:46,387
You shot him at point blank
and threw him off a roof.

477
00:46:46,470 --> 00:46:48,472
I'd hardly call that showing restraint,

478
00:46:48,556 --> 00:46:51,056
especially since he was a
member of Special Branch.

479
00:46:54,520 --> 00:46:55,647
So who was he guarding?

480
00:46:55,730 --> 00:46:56,814
Bond, are you missing the fact

481
00:46:56,897 --> 00:46:58,358
that you killed a member
of Special Branch?

482
00:46:58,441 --> 00:47:00,401
I need you to come in.

483
00:47:00,484 --> 00:47:02,598
And I would, but right now I need to

484
00:47:02,599 --> 00:47:04,655
find the man who tried to kill you.

485
00:47:04,739 --> 00:47:05,865
Go back to sleep.

486
00:47:05,948 --> 00:47:07,241
Connection terminated.

487
00:47:07,325 --> 00:47:08,743
Restrict Bond's movements.

488
00:47:08,826 --> 00:47:10,494
Cancel his cards.

489
00:47:10,578 --> 00:47:12,288
Put an alert on his
passports. All of them.

490
00:47:12,371 --> 00:47:14,624
And I want to know everything
we don't know about Haines.

491
00:47:14,707 --> 00:47:15,750
Yes, ma'am.

492
00:47:15,833 --> 00:47:18,961
And, Tanner, be careful
who you trust with this.

493
00:47:19,045 --> 00:47:21,795
Hopefully, you're a better
judge of character than I am.

494
00:47:23,049 --> 00:47:25,468
You want to follow your
friends to La Paz, Bolivia?

495
00:47:25,551 --> 00:47:26,844
Please.

496
00:47:29,263 --> 00:47:30,848
I'm sorry, sir, but this doesn't work.

497
00:47:30,931 --> 00:47:33,225
Do you have another card?

498
00:47:33,309 --> 00:47:34,518
No.

499
00:47:39,940 --> 00:47:41,901
Could you do me a favour?

500
00:47:41,984 --> 00:47:43,861
You're gonna get a phone call in a minute.

501
00:47:43,944 --> 00:47:47,365
Would you mind telling
them I'm headed for Cairo?

502
00:47:47,448 --> 00:47:49,784
- I'd be happy to.
- Thank you.

503
00:47:54,800 --> 00:47:56,300
(GREETING IN GERMAN)

504
00:48:29,824 --> 00:48:31,158
Mathis.

505
00:48:31,951 --> 00:48:33,786
What do you want?

506
00:48:33,869 --> 00:48:35,538
Come to apologise?

507
00:48:37,998 --> 00:48:39,708
You know, Mathis,

508
00:48:40,292 --> 00:48:42,503
I think retirement suits you.

509
00:48:43,295 --> 00:48:44,839
None for him.

510
00:48:45,381 --> 00:48:47,675
Sorry. He's in a bad mood today.

511
00:48:47,925 --> 00:48:50,646
This man had me imprisoned and tortured

512
00:48:51,040 --> 00:48:53,157
and you want to serve him fine wine?

513
00:48:53,433 --> 00:48:55,066
You only buy cheap wine.

514
00:48:56,726 --> 00:49:00,304
And since you were innocent, they
bought you this villa.

515
00:49:00,484 --> 00:49:02,529
So really you owe him, don't you?

516
00:49:04,188 --> 00:49:07,025
Gemma, go work on your tan.

517
00:49:11,240 --> 00:49:14,243
I need a passport and
matching credit cards.

518
00:49:14,326 --> 00:49:16,537
And MI6 ran out of plastic?

519
00:49:17,913 --> 00:49:20,625
Well, oddly, right now, you're the
only person I think I can trust.

520
00:49:20,708 --> 00:49:22,376
That is odd.

521
00:49:22,460 --> 00:49:24,295
But I guess when one's young,

522
00:49:24,378 --> 00:49:28,090
it seems very easy to distinguish
between right and wrong.

523
00:49:28,174 --> 00:49:31,135
But as one gets older, it
becomes more difficult.

524
00:49:31,218 --> 00:49:34,221
The villains and the
heroes get all mixed up.

525
00:49:35,222 --> 00:49:37,600
I was sorry to hear about Vesper.

526
00:49:38,142 --> 00:49:40,019
I think she loved you.

527
00:49:41,103 --> 00:49:43,481
Right up until the moment she betrayed me.

528
00:49:44,398 --> 00:49:46,066
She died for you.

529
00:49:48,110 --> 00:49:50,529
Why did you really want to see me?

530
00:49:52,156 --> 00:49:54,074
I need some information.

531
00:49:58,245 --> 00:50:02,458
You have some hard friends. This
man is some kind of facilitator.

532
00:50:02,583 --> 00:50:05,920
Fingers in many pies, and
they don't leave any prints.

533
00:50:06,003 --> 00:50:09,632
- These men were together?
- They're buying up oil pipeline.

534
00:50:09,715 --> 00:50:11,217
Something called the Tierra Project.

535
00:50:11,300 --> 00:50:13,677
- Do you know it?
- Destroy these.

536
00:50:13,761 --> 00:50:16,138
That's Guy Haines.
You don't know him?

537
00:50:16,222 --> 00:50:18,182
- Should I?
- I suppose not.

538
00:50:18,265 --> 00:50:21,352
You haven't been keeping
secrets as long as I have.

539
00:50:21,435 --> 00:50:23,354
He keeps a very low profile,

540
00:50:23,437 --> 00:50:27,107
but he's one of the Prime
Minister's closest advisors.

541
00:50:27,191 --> 00:50:30,778
Well, they say you're judged by
the strength of your enemies.

542
00:50:30,861 --> 00:50:33,030
Do you know anything about Bolivia?

543
00:50:33,113 --> 00:50:36,283
I was stationed in South
America for seven years.

544
00:50:36,367 --> 00:50:38,526
Well, do you have some contacts there?

545
00:50:38,527 --> 00:50:39,545
A few.

546
00:50:39,703 --> 00:50:41,789
What do you want to know?

547
00:50:42,665 --> 00:50:44,124
Come with me.

548
00:50:49,281 --> 00:50:51,454
I want your hands on my skin.

549
00:51:14,863 --> 00:51:16,657
You can't sleep?

550
00:51:17,241 --> 00:51:19,076
May I fix you a drink, sir?

551
00:51:19,159 --> 00:51:21,078
What are you drinking?

552
00:51:21,829 --> 00:51:23,831
I don't know. What am I drinking?

553
00:51:23,914 --> 00:51:27,258
Three measures of Gordon's
gin, one of vodka, half of...

554
00:51:27,259 --> 00:51:28,259
Kina Lillet.

555
00:51:28,264 --> 00:51:30,504
Kina Lillet, which is not Vermouth,

556
00:51:30,588 --> 00:51:32,298
shaken well until it is ice-cold,

557
00:51:32,381 --> 00:51:35,676
then served with a large
thin slice of lemon peel.

558
00:51:36,260 --> 00:51:37,761
Six of them.

559
00:51:38,095 --> 00:51:39,763
That's impressive.

560
00:51:39,847 --> 00:51:42,224
They're good. You should have one.

561
00:51:42,308 --> 00:51:44,852
No, it'll just keep me awake.

562
00:51:49,231 --> 00:51:51,567
So what's keeping you awake?

563
00:51:54,320 --> 00:51:56,989
I was wondering why you came with me.

564
00:51:58,574 --> 00:52:01,785
It takes something to
admit you were wrong.

565
00:52:04,830 --> 00:52:07,166
- You want a sleeping pill?
- No.

566
00:52:07,249 --> 00:52:08,876
- Pain pill?
- No.

567
00:52:08,959 --> 00:52:11,086
I have pills for everything.

568
00:52:11,587 --> 00:52:13,547
Some make you taller.

569
00:52:14,673 --> 00:52:16,550
Some make you forget.

570
00:52:19,845 --> 00:52:22,264
I'm going to try and get some sleep.

571
00:52:22,348 --> 00:52:23,724
Good idea.

572
00:52:38,697 --> 00:52:40,074
Thank you.

573
00:52:40,574 --> 00:52:43,535
Mr Bond, my name is Fields.
I'm from the consulate.

574
00:52:43,619 --> 00:52:44,620
Well, of course you are.

575
00:52:44,703 --> 00:52:46,137
And what do you do at
the consulate, Fields?

576
00:52:46,138 --> 00:52:47,414
That's not important.

577
00:52:47,498 --> 00:52:48,749
My orders are to turn you around

578
00:52:48,832 --> 00:52:50,876
and put you on the first
plane back to London.

579
00:52:50,959 --> 00:52:53,712
Do those orders include my friend Mathis?

580
00:52:53,796 --> 00:52:55,506
I'm sorry, I don't know who you are.

581
00:52:55,589 --> 00:52:58,759
You see that? Gone such a short
time and already forgotten.

582
00:52:58,842 --> 00:53:00,553
You're just saying that to hurt me.

583
00:53:00,636 --> 00:53:03,764
Mr Bond, these orders come from
the highest possible authority.

584
00:53:03,847 --> 00:53:06,809
Taxi. Fields, when is the
next flight to London?

585
00:53:06,892 --> 00:53:08,310
Tomorrow morning.

586
00:53:08,394 --> 00:53:09,395
Well then, we have all night.

587
00:53:09,478 --> 00:53:11,063
If you attempt to flee, I will arrest you,

588
00:53:11,146 --> 00:53:13,608
drop you off in jail and take
you to the plane in chains.

589
00:53:13,691 --> 00:53:16,235
- Understand?
- Perfectly. After you.

590
00:53:18,237 --> 00:53:21,073
- I think she has handcuffs.
- I do hope so.

591
00:53:29,790 --> 00:53:32,090
He blames the water
shortage on global warming.

592
00:53:32,960 --> 00:53:34,086
{\an8}Hello, Carlos? Carlos.

593
00:53:38,298 --> 00:53:40,426
{\an8}The Colonel who heads the National Police.

594
00:54:05,743 --> 00:54:07,786
We have a reservation.

595
00:54:08,579 --> 00:54:10,081
- Cémo esté?
- Very well, thank you.

596
00:54:10,164 --> 00:54:12,541
- Your name?
- Miss Fields.

597
00:54:17,296 --> 00:54:19,173
- You're going nowhere.
- So shoot me.

598
00:54:19,256 --> 00:54:20,257
I'd rather stay in a morgue.

599
00:54:20,340 --> 00:54:23,594
We are teachers on sabbatical.
This fits our cover.

600
00:54:23,677 --> 00:54:26,430
No, it doesn't. Get in. Get in.

601
00:54:52,873 --> 00:54:54,541
Follow me, please.

602
00:55:02,132 --> 00:55:03,587
May I show you your room, senior?

603
00:55:03,588 --> 00:55:04,838
No, it's fine. Thank you.

604
00:55:22,653 --> 00:55:24,822
I can't find the...

605
00:55:25,614 --> 00:55:27,241
The stationery.

606
00:55:28,116 --> 00:55:30,327
Will you come and help me look?

607
00:55:44,591 --> 00:55:46,760
You've been invited to a party.

608
00:55:46,844 --> 00:55:49,471
I didn't know we had any friends here.

609
00:55:50,514 --> 00:55:52,057
Greene Planet.

610
00:55:53,267 --> 00:55:54,268
You're not coming?

611
00:55:54,351 --> 00:55:56,520
I'm having a drink with
my friend the Colonel.

612
00:55:56,603 --> 00:55:58,939
I'll see you there later.

613
00:56:03,902 --> 00:56:06,613
Do you know how angry I am at myself?

614
00:56:07,114 --> 00:56:08,866
I can't imagine.

615
00:56:11,618 --> 00:56:13,495
You must be furious.

616
00:56:20,043 --> 00:56:22,296
Do you want to go to a party?

617
00:56:22,963 --> 00:56:24,172
A party?

618
00:56:25,007 --> 00:56:27,134
But I have nothing to wear.

619
00:56:27,551 --> 00:56:28,635
We'll fix that.

620
00:56:48,238 --> 00:56:50,574
It might be useful to know your real name.

621
00:56:50,657 --> 00:56:52,075
Fields.

622
00:56:54,703 --> 00:56:56,204
Just Fields.

623
00:56:57,205 --> 00:56:58,832
Fields it is, then.

624
00:56:58,916 --> 00:57:02,711
We are in a spiral of
environmental decline.

625
00:57:03,837 --> 00:57:09,927
Since 1945, 17% of the
planet's vegetated surface

626
00:57:10,010 --> 00:57:12,888
has been irreversibly degraded.

627
00:57:13,680 --> 00:57:16,335
The Tierra Project is just one small

628
00:57:16,336 --> 00:57:19,061
part of a global network of ECO Parks

629
00:57:19,144 --> 00:57:21,188
that Greene Planet has created

630
00:57:21,271 --> 00:57:25,692
to rejuvenate a world on
the verge of collapse.

631
00:57:27,444 --> 00:57:31,657
I hope that tonight you make the
decision to be part of that.

632
00:57:33,700 --> 00:57:35,035
Thank you.

633
00:57:39,289 --> 00:57:40,791
And have fun.

634
00:57:41,375 --> 00:57:43,543
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

635
00:57:44,294 --> 00:57:46,338
Excellent speech and congratulations.

636
00:57:46,421 --> 00:57:48,548
Wonderful speech, Dominic.

637
00:57:48,632 --> 00:57:50,550
- We need you here.
- Thank you.

638
00:57:50,634 --> 00:57:53,929
Miss Fields, Mr Bond, my friend Carlos.

639
00:57:54,012 --> 00:57:55,889
- Pleased to meet you.
- Ma'am.

640
00:57:56,974 --> 00:57:59,935
Mr Bond, Mathis has spoken
a great deal about you.

641
00:58:00,018 --> 00:58:03,897
I want you to know my entire
police force is at your disposal.

642
00:58:04,272 --> 00:58:05,691
Well, that could be very useful.

643
00:58:05,774 --> 00:58:07,269
You know, there are people in this

644
00:58:07,270 --> 00:58:09,028
country spending half their pay cheque

645
00:58:09,111 --> 00:58:10,612
just to get clean water.

646
00:58:10,696 --> 00:58:11,739
What do you think of that?

647
00:58:11,822 --> 00:58:13,907
The Bolivian government is the problem.

648
00:58:13,991 --> 00:58:15,659
They cut down the trees,

649
00:58:15,742 --> 00:58:19,871
then act surprised when the water
and the soil wash out to sea.

650
00:58:19,955 --> 00:58:23,458
I couldn't agree more. I hope
this figure is to your liking.

651
00:58:23,542 --> 00:58:25,919
Chéri, you shouldn't tease.

652
00:58:26,003 --> 00:58:28,080
Why don't you tell them about all the

653
00:58:28,081 --> 00:58:30,048
land you bought up outside Potosi'?

654
00:58:30,132 --> 00:58:32,342
It's been a pleasure.
Will you excuse me?

655
00:58:32,426 --> 00:58:33,760
Of course.

656
00:58:33,844 --> 00:58:35,012
Somehow the logging rights

657
00:58:35,095 --> 00:58:37,430
went to a multinational corporation

658
00:58:37,431 --> 00:58:39,182
that out down the forests,

659
00:58:39,266 --> 00:58:44,021
but only after our last government
sold the land to Greene Planet.

660
00:58:45,939 --> 00:58:49,317
- Or have I got my facts crossed?
- Yes, I think you did.

661
00:58:50,110 --> 00:58:51,987
You'll excuse us?

662
00:58:52,779 --> 00:58:54,740
What a wonderful night.

663
00:58:58,035 --> 00:59:00,620
You just cost me quite a
bit of money, darling.

664
00:59:00,704 --> 00:59:03,415
You can't put a price on integrity.

665
00:59:03,498 --> 00:59:04,575
I can try.

666
00:59:04,624 --> 00:59:05,625
Oh.

667
00:59:10,589 --> 00:59:11,882
Thank you.

668
00:59:11,965 --> 00:59:15,927
Tell me you didn't drop by tonight
just to piss on my parade.

669
00:59:16,011 --> 00:59:19,931
Or are you still after this
General's head for your mantel?

670
00:59:20,015 --> 00:59:21,558
A little of both.

671
00:59:21,641 --> 00:59:23,101
Tell me where Medrano is

672
00:59:23,185 --> 00:59:26,313
and maybe you won't lose
any more investors.

673
00:59:29,858 --> 00:59:31,884
You are really breaking my heart,

674
00:59:31,885 --> 00:59:34,279
choosing an insect like that over me.

675
00:59:35,822 --> 00:59:37,532
Are you going to throw me over?

676
00:59:37,616 --> 00:59:40,911
No. You've been drinking,
so maybe you slipped.

677
00:59:41,703 --> 00:59:44,206
Oh. Just think how
much you'd miss me.

678
00:59:49,669 --> 00:59:51,171
Good evening.

679
00:59:51,254 --> 00:59:52,839
There you are.

680
00:59:54,674 --> 00:59:56,635
Would you excuse me?

681
00:59:56,718 --> 00:59:58,053
Mr Bond.

682
00:59:59,096 --> 01:00:00,722
What a pleasure.

683
01:00:02,891 --> 01:00:05,102
Well, careful with this one.
She won't go to bed with you

684
01:00:05,185 --> 01:00:07,854
unless you give her
something she really wants.

685
01:00:07,938 --> 01:00:10,107
It's a shame because she's
really quite stunning

686
01:00:10,190 --> 01:00:12,984
once you get her on her back.

687
01:00:13,068 --> 01:00:15,737
I wish I could say the feeling was mutual.

688
01:00:15,821 --> 01:00:17,121
I'm sorry, Mr Greene, but we have to go.

689
01:00:17,197 --> 01:00:19,491
Please. My friends
call me Dominic.

690
01:00:19,574 --> 01:00:21,284
I'm sure they do.

691
01:00:22,285 --> 01:00:24,746
How much do you know about Bond, Camille?

692
01:00:24,830 --> 01:00:27,124
Because he's rather a tragic case.

693
01:00:27,207 --> 01:00:30,127
As MI6 says, he's difficult to control.

694
01:00:30,210 --> 01:00:32,427
Nice way of saying that everything

695
01:00:32,428 --> 01:00:34,840
he touches seems to wither and die.

696
01:00:34,923 --> 01:00:36,133
Shall we?

697
01:00:36,216 --> 01:00:38,760
Doesn't bode well for you, I'm afraid.

698
01:00:38,844 --> 01:00:40,929
You two do make a charming couple, though.

699
01:00:41,012 --> 01:00:43,932
You're both... What's
the expression?

700
01:00:44,015 --> 01:00:45,642
Damaged goods.

701
01:00:49,062 --> 01:00:50,564
Oh, my gosh.

702
01:00:51,523 --> 01:00:53,066
I'm so sorry.

703
01:00:56,778 --> 01:00:57,946
Come on, lighten up.

704
01:00:58,029 --> 01:01:00,073
You're cramping my style.

705
01:01:01,032 --> 01:01:02,993
So it's British intelligence now.

706
01:01:03,076 --> 01:01:04,620
What the hell do you want from me?

707
01:01:04,703 --> 01:01:07,455
You're gonna show me Dominic
Greene's Tierra Project.

708
01:01:07,539 --> 01:01:09,583
- Are you up to it?
- Do I have a choice?

709
01:01:09,666 --> 01:01:11,459
Do you want one?

710
01:01:11,543 --> 01:01:14,421
There's something horribly
efficient about you.

711
01:01:14,504 --> 01:01:16,339
Is that a compliment?

712
01:01:29,644 --> 01:01:31,616
Well, what's the bet that Dominic

713
01:01:31,617 --> 01:01:34,065
Greene has friends in the police force?

714
01:01:45,202 --> 01:01:46,745
Stay here.

715
01:01:51,707 --> 01:01:53,228
Papers, please.

716
01:02:03,739 --> 01:02:05,259
Open the trunk.

717
01:02:07,641 --> 01:02:10,268
Now, why would you want me to do that?

718
01:02:13,686 --> 01:02:14,686
Get him out.

719
01:02:15,280 --> 01:02:16,280
Hurry up.

720
01:02:17,581 --> 01:02:18,581
Get him out.

721
01:02:24,767 --> 01:02:25,767
He's moving.

722
01:02:25,861 --> 01:02:26,861
Shoot him.

723
01:02:41,716 --> 01:02:43,051
Mathis?

724
01:02:44,970 --> 01:02:48,014
There's a hospital on
the other side of town.

725
01:02:48,098 --> 01:02:49,474
Please.

726
01:02:50,517 --> 01:02:52,269
Stay with me.

727
01:02:52,852 --> 01:02:54,604
Stay here, please.

728
01:02:55,480 --> 01:02:56,731
Please.

729
01:02:57,148 --> 01:02:58,525
Come here.

730
01:03:01,903 --> 01:03:03,363
It's okay.

731
01:03:05,282 --> 01:03:06,825
That's better.

732
01:03:07,117 --> 01:03:08,868
That doesn't hurt.

733
01:03:11,997 --> 01:03:14,124
Is Mathis your cover name?

734
01:03:15,166 --> 01:03:16,376
Yes.

735
01:03:18,503 --> 01:03:20,630
Not a very good one, is it?

736
01:03:26,261 --> 01:03:28,513
Do we forgive each other?

737
01:03:30,849 --> 01:03:33,268
I shouldn't have left you alone.

738
01:03:34,894 --> 01:03:36,229
Vesper.

739
01:03:37,439 --> 01:03:39,607
She gave everything for you.

740
01:03:41,985 --> 01:03:43,403
Forgive her.

741
01:03:45,530 --> 01:03:47,324
Forgive yourself.

742
01:04:08,636 --> 01:04:11,181
Is that how you treat your friends?

743
01:04:12,599 --> 01:04:14,267
He wouldn't care.

744
01:04:20,482 --> 01:04:21,900
Let's go.

745
01:04:36,122 --> 01:04:39,125
The Foreign Secretary's asking to see you.

746
01:04:39,667 --> 01:04:41,044
What don't I know?

747
01:04:41,127 --> 01:04:44,172
Rene Mathis has been shot dead in Bolivia.

748
01:04:44,672 --> 01:04:46,966
The police claim it was Bond.

749
01:05:21,292 --> 01:05:22,502
How much did you pay him?

750
01:05:22,585 --> 01:05:25,922
Well, he wanted you, but I left
him the car as collateral.

751
01:05:26,005 --> 01:05:28,967
He'll make much more when he sells us out.

752
01:05:31,678 --> 01:05:32,887
Right.

753
01:05:33,221 --> 01:05:35,765
Let's see if this thing'll fly.

754
01:05:50,822 --> 01:05:51,948
Here.

755
01:05:52,031 --> 01:05:55,577
All the information I found said
there was nothing of value there,

756
01:05:55,660 --> 01:05:58,830
but Greene's geologist had
proof that there was.

757
01:06:02,208 --> 01:06:05,628
My sources tell me you're
Bolivian Secret Service,

758
01:06:06,671 --> 01:06:08,339
or used to be,

759
01:06:09,257 --> 01:06:10,847
and that you infiltrated Greene's

760
01:06:10,848 --> 01:06:12,677
organisation by having sex with him.

761
01:06:13,595 --> 01:06:16,598
- That offends you?
- No, not in the slightest.

762
01:06:17,015 --> 01:06:19,225
So what's your interest in Greene?

763
01:06:19,309 --> 01:06:22,353
Amongst other things, he tried
to kill a friend of mine.

764
01:06:22,437 --> 01:06:23,938
- A woman?
- Yes.

765
01:06:24,397 --> 01:06:25,940
But it's not what you think.

766
01:06:26,024 --> 01:06:28,860
- Your mother?
- She likes to think so.

767
01:06:32,697 --> 01:06:34,741
What's that down there?

768
01:06:37,243 --> 01:06:38,912
That's a sinkhole.

769
01:06:38,995 --> 01:06:41,247
There are a few around here.

770
01:06:42,248 --> 01:06:45,585
Just for the record, I
wasn't with Greene for my...

771
01:07:20,745 --> 01:07:22,038
Damn it.

772
01:07:51,442 --> 01:07:53,278
I think we lost him.

773
01:08:02,662 --> 01:08:04,372
He's coming fast.

774
01:08:51,336 --> 01:08:53,379
He's right behind you.

775
01:09:35,213 --> 01:09:37,215
Here. Put that on.

776
01:10:22,135 --> 01:10:23,511
Come on.

777
01:10:44,657 --> 01:10:45,950
Camille.

778
01:11:05,178 --> 01:11:07,597
According to the Bolivians,
it was a routine stop,

779
01:11:07,680 --> 01:11:10,684
and when they discovered Mathis'
body, Bond disarmed and shot them.

780
01:11:10,767 --> 01:11:12,894
Of course, there are no
witnesses to prove otherwise.

781
01:11:12,977 --> 01:11:15,772
I need something. I can't
go in there unarmed.

782
01:11:15,855 --> 01:11:17,982
I'm sorry. There's nothing.

783
01:11:20,359 --> 01:11:21,694
Come in.

784
01:11:23,154 --> 01:11:26,616
What's today's excuse? That
Bond is legally blind?

785
01:11:26,699 --> 01:11:27,825
No, Minister.

786
01:11:27,909 --> 01:11:30,703
I don't think I need to tell
you how upset the P.M. is.

787
01:11:31,078 --> 01:11:33,664
With respect, the P.M.
has my direct line.

788
01:11:33,748 --> 01:11:37,293
And he'd have used it if
he'd wanted to speak to you.

789
01:11:37,376 --> 01:11:39,879
I'm sorry, M. Things have changed.

790
01:11:40,505 --> 01:11:43,132
We've had long discussions
with our cousins.

791
01:11:43,216 --> 01:11:45,468
Mr Greene's interests and ours now align.

